29/02/2008
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- A bomb threat called in to parliament on Thursday (February 28th) postponed debate on the new cabinet, to be led by Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic. The threat was received shortly after Djukanovic presented his platform. After the building was evacuated, a search turned up no evidence of any explosives. Djukanovic agreed to return to the helm of government and replace Zeljko Sturanovic, who resigned after being diagnosed with a cancer. (Vijesti - 29/02/08; Antena M, RTCG, BIRN, AFP - 28/02/08)
